<Content>My 2nd home in Mexico As a flight attendant I travel the world for a living. I spend several weeks here every year since 1998. Request a room with a small balcony with a door that opens over the Avenue( Rep. de Uruguay). the owner is usually very friendly and helpful. This hotel is very basic, some have tv's others not. It is usually well-kept, clean, and even serves to park cars through the lobby throughout the day. Rates are from 10 to 15 us/day. Only 2 blocks from the Zocalo and the metro station Pino Suarez or either Isabel la Catholica. The Palacio de Bellas Artes is nearby too, as are a lot of history and architecture. Enjoy Mexico City and this hotel as much as I have and continue to . Better from single travelers by far. If you're a family, spend more somewhere else. If you're up for adventure, choose MonteCarlo. This is also where D. H. Lawrence did some of his writings, fyi. Enjoy your stay. Nos vemos, stace 
