<Content>Good place, good location I stayed in this place for four nights in December 2002. It's near Hotel Isabel, but on a quieter street, which should mean less street noise and a quieter place in general but also a walk down a dark narrow street late at night. I had no problems at all in the centro historico, but women or nervous types might prefer someplace else. The rooms are nice, but if you stay during the pollution season (winter, for example) be sure to plug up the door and close the windows before you go to bed to keep out the smog in the morning. My room was on an open courtyard and the smog comes right inside. After morning the smog cleared up a lot and it was fine. 
